We have, $P^2=I-P$
<br/><br/>$$
\begin{aligned}
\Rightarrow P^4 & =(I-P)^2=I+P^2-2 P \\\\
& =2 I-3 P \text { [Using Eq. (i)] }
\end{aligned}
$$
<br/><br/>$$
\begin{aligned}
\Rightarrow P^8 & =(2 I-3 P)^2 \\\\
& =4 I+9 P^2-12 P \\\\
& =13 I-21 P \text { [Using Eq. (i)] }
\end{aligned}
$$
<br/><br/>and
<br/><br/>$$
\begin{aligned}
P^6 & =(I-P)(2 I-3 P) \\\\
& =2 I-3 P-2 P+3 P^2 \\\\
& =5 I-8 P \text { [Using Eq. (i)] }
\end{aligned}
$$
<br/><br/>$\begin{aligned} & \text { Now, } P^8+P^6=18 I-29 P \\\\ & \text { and } P^8-P^6=8 I-13 P \\\\ & \therefore \alpha=8, \beta=6, \gamma=18, \delta=8 \\\\ & \therefore \alpha+\beta+\gamma-\delta=8+6+18-8=24\end{aligned}$

